speech.p:
(1) To authorise the payment, out of moneys provided by Parliament, of—


(a) any increase in the sums, payable out of moneys so provided which is attributable to any provisions of the said Act raising by five hundred thousand pounds the limit imposed by subsection (1) of section five of the White Fish and Herring Industries Act, 1948, upon the aggregate amount of the grants which may be made under that subsection out of

moneys so provided and enabling that limit to be further raised by an amount not exceeding two hundred and fifty thousand pounds;

(b) any expenses incurred by the Minister of Agriculture and Fisheries and the Secretary of State in giving, to public authorities or associations of persons or companies not trading for profit, financial assistance in respect of—


(i) the execution of works for the construction, improvement or repair of harbours, piers, quays, jetties, boatslips or slipways in Great Britain, the landward approaches thereto or buildings, structures or apparatus thereat;

(ii) costs incurred in or in connection with the preparation of plans and specifications of such works, reports with respect thereto and estimates of expenses to be incurred for the purposes of the execution thereof; or

(iii) the remuneration of persons employed in an advisory or supervisory capacity in connection with the execution of such works;

(c)any expenses incurred by the Minister of Agriculture and Fisheries or the Secretary of State by virtue of any provision of the said Act vesting in the one or the other of them liabilities of the Treasury under agreements made by the Treasury for the making, under Part I of the Development and Road Improvement Funds Act, 1909, of advances for the construction or improvement of harbours; and

(d) any expenses incurred by the Secretary of State in operating dredgers;
